    TAG USED TO CONNECT(OR JUMPT TO OTH WEBSITE)2 WEBPAGES IS <a>.href is a tag specific attribute
        <a> is initially a inline tag.when there is more than 1 <a> it can be made block level by using css property 
            by using display:block;.which makes teh 2nd a tag go to the next line
        if the link given is not correct then it shows error as  cannot get webpage_name
        There are 3 types of attributes in html
        1) tag specific
        2) global attribute
        3) event attribute
        ex: <a href="some url" id="mylink" onclick="dosomething();"></a>
        Here href is a tag specific attribute(i.e it can be only used with anchor tag)
        id is a global attribute(i.e which can be used with any tag,such as div,p,img etc..)
        onclick is an event attribute
        <dd> tag is used to move the selected character inside the tag to be shown in the new line.
