    block level tags are always parent and inline tags are
CSS` code always starts just before ending of head tag and starts officially with <style></style> tag
 
  in the above codered is the value,color is the property,div signifies the element/tag .
  CSS selectors are used to find the html elements we want to style
  they are divided into 5 categories
  : simple selector(select tags based on certain state)
  :combination selectors(select tags based on a soecific relationship between them)
  :pseudo class selectors: select and style a part of a tag
  : attribute selectors:(selects tags based on a attribute/attribute value)
    selector in css: it is used to select html elements which we wamt to style
 1) simple selector:(select elemts bases on name ,id class)
 synatx:  tag {
    property(which we want to change):value;
 }   
ex: div{
    color:red;
}
simple selector backlift: it applies same filter to all selcted images,files etcc
2): ID SELECTOR: it is used to ASSIGN DIFFERENT properties TO ELEMENTS OF HTML PROG AND ALSO DIFF PROPERTIES
syntax:  element#id_name
{
    PROPERTY:VALUE(<img src="" id="id_name">) id name should always start and end with alphabet
}

